.:: Zebra puzzle ::.
House: colonial, townhouse, palace, victorian, craftsman
There are 5 different nationalities: english, spanish, ukranian, norwegian, japanese
City: boston, rome, london, paris, san-francisco
The people prefer 5 different types of sport: badminton, biathlon, soccer, sailing, water-polo
5 different games are played: domino, backgammon, snooker, billiard, mah-jongg

1. the english is the colonial house
2. the spanish is the person playing domino
3. the person who's sport is badminton is the townhouse house
4. the ukranian is the person who's sport is biathlon
5. the townhouse house is to the right of the palace house
6. the person traveling to boston is the person playing mah-jongg
7. the person traveling to rome is the victorian house
8. the person who's sport is soccer is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the person traveling to london is on the left or right of the person playing backgammon
11. the person traveling to rome is to the left or right of the person playing billiard
12. the person traveling to paris is the person who's sport is sailing
13. the japanese is the person traveling to san-francisco
14. the norwegian is to the left or right of the craftsman house

.:: Answer ::.
